WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:47.180 --> 00:50.274
<i>(woman)</i> You don't know
where you're going.

00:50.350 --> 00:53.217
Yes, I do.

00:53.286 --> 00:57.620
- You don't know where you are.
- Yes, I do. I'm in hell.

00:57.690 --> 01:02.923
Just get in the car.
You cannot walk the entire way to...

01:04.063 --> 01:07.158
- This was your choice.
- This was not my choice, Mom.

01:07.233 --> 01:11.761
What, to live with some old bitch
that you can't even stand that I don't even know?

01:11.838 --> 01:14.602
You wanted me out of your life,
I'm out of your life, Mom.

01:14.674 --> 01:17.074
You're impossible. You are impossible.

01:17.143 --> 01:19.338
If you weren't such a nutcase,

01:19.412 --> 01:22.870
we could have flown here
like normal people and been done with this shit.

01:22.949 --> 01:26.407
You won, OK? You won.
I'm out of your life.

01:26.486 --> 01:29.546
- No one has won.
- I'm out of your life.

01:29.622 --> 01:32.750
Now if you please would just get out of mine.

01:32.826 --> 01:35.556
- Go. Get out.
- All right, fine.

02:10.029 --> 02:11.997
<i>(truck radio playing)</i>

02:33.353 --> 02:35.446
<i>(music stops)</i>

02:42.996 --> 02:45.089
<i>(man)</i> Hello?

02:59.012 --> 03:00.536
- <i>(screams)</i>
- Hey! Whoa!

03:00.613 --> 03:03.275
Whoa, whoa! Hey, hey, hey!

03:03.349 --> 03:06.011
Who are you?

03:06.085 --> 03:08.553
Hey, I didn't mean nothing.
Just calm down.

03:08.621 --> 03:12.079
My God, are you one of those
back-country sodomy boys?

03:12.158 --> 03:14.820
I didn't mean any harm.

03:15.895 --> 03:18.227
Can you help me up, please?

03:19.532 --> 03:22.296
- Are you crazy?
- No.

03:22.368 --> 03:24.233
I'm Rachel.

03:24.304 --> 03:27.000
- Harlan Wilson.
- <i>(dog barks)</i>

03:27.073 --> 03:29.837
You got yourself a nice feel there,
didn't you, Harlan Wilson?

03:29.909 --> 03:33.242
- Hey, that wasn't my intention.
- What were your intentions?

03:33.313 --> 03:36.111
- To see if you were dead.
- <i>(honks horn)</i>

03:36.182 --> 03:38.173
<i>(dog barks)</i>

03:38.818 --> 03:40.843
Car trouble, Harlan?

03:41.487 --> 03:44.547
Hey, I had one of these.
Till I crashed it. Can I drive?

03:44.624 --> 03:48.060
- Beg your pardon?
- I found her sleeping by the side of the road.

03:48.127 --> 03:50.857
Come on, let's go. Let's go.

03:50.930 --> 03:53.330
- Says her name's Rachel.
- Yeah?

03:53.399 --> 03:57.199
If she turns out to be sane...
you know, she's all yours.

03:57.270 --> 04:00.535
- I gotta get back to work.
- Hey.

04:00.607 --> 04:04.634
Is for horses. Better for cows.
Pigs don't eat it 'cause they don't know how.

04:04.711 --> 04:07.908
- What's your name?
- Simon.

04:07.981 --> 04:08.913
Hmm.

04:10.350 --> 04:12.682
- I wasn't really going anywhere.
- That's where I'm going.

04:12.752 --> 04:13.878
- Where?
- Anywhere.

04:13.953 --> 04:17.116
- I was going there alone.
- Now you're not. Consider yourself lucky.

04:17.190 --> 04:21.718
- I would if you weren't here.
- Mm. Consider yourself stuck.

04:23.763 --> 04:26.527
<i>(starts engine/drives off)</i>

04:27.233 --> 04:30.964
- <i>(Simon)</i> I don't like to talk.
- <i>(Rachel)</i> Perfect. I don't like to listen.

04:35.475 --> 04:36.635
<i>(sighs)</i>

04:41.381 --> 04:45.147
- Would you put your legs back in my car?
- Changing the rules?

04:45.218 --> 04:49.678
There were no rules.
Other than no parts of your body outside my car.

04:49.756 --> 04:52.782
- Well, then, can I talk to you?
- Put your legs down.

04:52.859 --> 04:55.794
You didn't say "Simon says," Simon.

04:58.164 --> 05:02.191
- I'm only going as far as Hull.
- Hull, Idaho? That's where I'm staying.

05:02.268 --> 05:04.395
My luck.

05:04.470 --> 05:07.837
Now, do you need to call someone,
or are you a surprise?

05:07.907 --> 05:13.106
I would. My mother cut my phone service off.
She's a gem.

05:45.945 --> 05:50.939
Nuh-uh. Ace is only low.
Not high. Georgia rule.

05:51.017 --> 05:54.009
Everybody else plays the right way.
Why can't we?

05:54.087 --> 05:59.286
So if everybody took a poop in the middle of Main
Street you'd do it too? 'Cause they said it was right?

05:59.359 --> 06:01.953
- Probably.
- My leg is numb.

06:02.028 --> 06:04.462
Hey, no quitting.

06:04.530 --> 06:07.158
I got pains from my gluteus
shooting up and out my eyes

06:07.233 --> 06:10.259
from sitting on the floor
with two boneless children.

06:10.336 --> 06:13.203
Quitting?
Did you hear me say "quitting"?

06:18.144 --> 06:20.135
<i>(dog barking)</i>

06:25.685 --> 06:26.982
Rummy.

06:27.053 --> 06:29.578
- Uhh.
- <i>(knock on door)</i>

06:29.655 --> 06:33.022
- Mom?
- Wait. No, we can't go. I'm winning.

06:34.293 --> 06:37.751
- Hello. You're not Mom.
- Hello.

06:37.830 --> 06:40.264
Lilly. Come on in.

06:43.836 --> 06:49.797
- Come on, boys. Erect me.
- She has gluten pains shooting out her eyeballs.

06:57.116 --> 06:59.482
Where's Rachel?

06:59.552 --> 07:05.548
I thought this drive would be good for us.
That we could talk, at least tolerate each other.

07:06.659 --> 07:09.025
Where is my granddaughter?

07:09.095 --> 07:11.427
She bolted from the car.

07:16.569 --> 07:19.402
You look really nice, anyway, Lilly.

07:19.472 --> 07:22.236
I should have put her on a plane.

07:22.308 --> 07:24.640
- Still smoke?
- No.

07:25.044 --> 07:29.947
Did I ask if you still dye your hair? I haven't had
a drink in years, in case you wanted to know.

07:30.016 --> 07:33.247
- It's none of my business.
- Yeah? Heh-heh.

07:33.319 --> 07:35.378
I brought you a gift.

07:35.455 --> 07:38.424
- Oh, it's lovely.
- How do you know?

07:38.491 --> 07:42.621
The ribbon and the paper. How's she gonna
find me? She's only been here once.

07:42.695 --> 07:45.721
13 years ago. Same as you.

07:45.798 --> 07:50.565
Rachel is very resourceful.
She'll find you when she needs you.

07:50.636 --> 07:52.695
Why are children in your house?

07:52.772 --> 07:57.141
They're my friends. Here, guys.
I watch them till their mom gets home.

07:57.210 --> 07:59.235
This is Sam. This is Ethan.

07:59.312 --> 08:02.179
- Nice to meet you.
- This is my daughter Lilly.

08:02.248 --> 08:03.476
Hi.

08:04.917 --> 08:10.355
Traveled all the way from San Francisco, California,
smelling of smoke. But she doesn't smoke.

08:10.423 --> 08:12.254
OK, Mother, caught me.

08:12.325 --> 08:15.522
Save the lies for something
more important than cancer.

08:15.595 --> 08:18.689
Why don't you go get the bags, you two?

08:18.764 --> 08:22.894
Oh, um, you know what?
Everything but the Louis Vuittons.

08:22.969 --> 08:26.200
They have "LV" written all over 'em.

08:28.407 --> 08:32.866
- You travel with luggage you don't use?
- Oh, I'm just staying a minute.

08:32.945 --> 08:37.678
I have friends. They're begging me
to come down to Salt Lake City and visit.

08:37.750 --> 08:40.183
Good friends?

08:40.253 --> 08:42.778
We keep in touch.

08:42.855 --> 08:45.323
Well, it's worth the drive, then.

08:48.261 --> 08:50.729
Bringing up the girl's bags.

08:50.796 --> 08:53.128
I think they got rocks in 'em.

08:56.602 --> 08:59.127
<i>(chirps)</i>

08:59.205 --> 09:02.800
Everything's exactly the same,
except for the bird.

09:04.443 --> 09:08.641
It's a glass... bedpan?

09:08.714 --> 09:11.979
Heh-heh. Crystal bowl. It's classy.

09:12.985 --> 09:16.250
- I thought of one for my mantel.
- Take this one, then.

09:16.322 --> 09:18.950
It's a gift, Mother.

09:19.725 --> 09:22.660
It's just there's so much on my mantel.

09:22.728 --> 09:26.061
Well, look around,
because I'm not taking it back.

09:26.132 --> 09:27.497
Thank you.

09:27.567 --> 09:30.968
It's lovely. Nice, thanks.

09:31.938 --> 09:36.932
- Well, this is Hull.
- Just drop me in town. Nice to know you, Simon.

09:37.009 --> 09:39.671
- You don't know me, kid.
- I know you.

09:39.745 --> 09:41.906
You do?

09:42.648 --> 09:45.879
I had my dress hiked and my legs up,
and you didn't look once.

09:45.952 --> 09:48.546
Not even for a second.

09:48.621 --> 09:50.816
So now you know me?

09:50.890 --> 09:54.792
No marriage ring.
What are you, 30? 40?

09:55.361 --> 09:57.352
You're gay.

10:02.902 --> 10:06.838
- All right, get out.
- I already asked you to let me out.

10:06.906 --> 10:11.843
- I'm telling you.
- What? You can't tell me what I've already asked.

10:11.911 --> 10:14.744
Get out. Just get out.

10:17.216 --> 10:21.152
I want my panties back
when you're done with them.

10:23.155 --> 10:27.057
Harlan found her sleeping
by the side of the road.

10:27.126 --> 10:30.562
- Do you buy that?
- He's a wonderful doctor.

10:30.630 --> 10:32.791
<i>(starts engine)</i>

10:48.014 --> 10:51.814
- Thanks for the sandwich.
- You won't make it to your friends' before dark.

10:51.884 --> 10:56.184
- That wasn't really my goal.
- Accidents mostly happen at dusk.

10:56.255 --> 11:00.191
- I would guess morning.
- Well, you'd be wrong.

11:00.259 --> 11:02.659
All in God's hands.

11:02.728 --> 11:05.561
- That's what your father always used to say.
- Uh-huh.

11:05.631 --> 11:08.065
Everybody's hands but his own.

11:09.101 --> 11:12.127
You never said anything bad about him
when he was alive.

11:12.204 --> 11:15.332
Well, if I did, why would I say it to you?

11:16.642 --> 11:21.739
Why say anything? Your granddaughter
takes off when she doesn't get her way.

11:21.814 --> 11:24.647
She's easy to find, though.
Just listen for a scream.

11:24.717 --> 11:30.713
If she doesn't show up in the next few hours,
call me on my cellphone, I'll turn around.

11:32.792 --> 11:35.192
Thank you for taking her.

11:35.561 --> 11:38.155
I hope it does her some good.

11:38.230 --> 11:40.698
Did it do you any good?

11:48.674 --> 11:49.663
<i>(starts engine)</i>

11:52.011 --> 11:54.571
<i># Beyond the horizon</i>

11:56.649 --> 11:59.083
<i># Behind the sun</i>

12:01.020 --> 12:04.751
<i># At the end of the rainbow</i>

12:04.824 --> 12:07.793
<i># Life has already begun</i>

12:09.695 --> 12:14.428
<i># In the long hours of twilight</i>

12:14.500 --> 12:17.264
<i># 'Neath the stardust above</i>

12:19.171 --> 12:21.662
<i># Beyond the horizon</i>

12:22.908 --> 12:25.172
<i># It is easy to love</i>

12:34.787 --> 12:36.345
- <i>(sighs)</i>
<i>- (sighs)</i>

12:37.423 --> 12:41.553
- Ahem. You don't look evil.
- Makeup helps.

12:41.627 --> 12:45.996
- Hmm. Where's my mom?
- Had to see friends.

12:46.065 --> 12:47.794
Oh, right.

12:47.867 --> 12:53.601
Did you hear the one where she's stopped smoking,
drinking and hating herself, too?

12:55.040 --> 12:56.871
<i>(sighs)</i> Rachel...

13:06.152 --> 13:08.416
I'm hungry.
Got anything with sugar?

13:08.487 --> 13:10.887
You're five hours late.

13:10.956 --> 13:14.653
My mother dumped me 20 miles out.
I had to walk the whole way.

13:14.727 --> 13:17.628
We eat at six. No exceptions.

13:17.696 --> 13:20.221
You'll have to wait for breakfast.

13:20.299 --> 13:23.132
Oh, there's apples on the table.

13:23.636 --> 13:28.972
Mm. Can I tell you what's really going on?
So we don't get lost in what this really is.

13:29.041 --> 13:31.874
I'd like to know.

13:32.678 --> 13:37.115
My mother and stepfather don't like my life.
Maybe because I have one, who knows?

13:37.183 --> 13:40.744
Anyway, I was stupid enough
to graduate high school in January.

13:40.820 --> 13:46.452
I got into a trouble a few times while I was waiting to
go to college in the fall. So they had to get rid of me.

13:46.525 --> 13:49.187
Banished for the summer in Idaho.

13:49.261 --> 13:53.163
Locked up with the one person on earth
my mother can't jerk around.

13:53.232 --> 13:55.257
That's why I'm here.

13:55.334 --> 13:57.928
Try and jerk me around, Grandma.

14:06.111 --> 14:08.875
Go fuck yourself.

14:11.550 --> 14:14.542
No good night kiss?

14:15.888 --> 14:16.946
OK.

14:19.458 --> 14:20.755
<i>(bell dings)</i>

15:11.777 --> 15:15.907
You know, the only picture
I've ever seen of you is with me in it.

15:15.981 --> 15:18.677
Holding this dog.

15:18.751 --> 15:22.881
I got it for you so you wouldn't be afraid
at your grandfather's funeral.

15:22.955 --> 15:25.185
You named it Grandpa.

15:25.257 --> 15:29.421
I was four. Couldn't you have helped me
pick a name that made some sense?

15:29.495 --> 15:32.089
It made sense to you.

15:33.732 --> 15:36.792
My stepfather promised
to buy me a new car for school.

15:36.869 --> 15:40.100
You know, if I can survive up here,
stay sane.

15:40.172 --> 15:43.801
Oh. So your time here
won't be a complete waste.

15:43.876 --> 15:46.242
Well, I'll miss my friends.

15:46.312 --> 15:51.511
Oh, cheer up. Most friends, in time,
become as useless as relatives.

16:05.230 --> 16:11.226
So, I brought seven novels. If I read them slowly,
that should kill two of the ten weeks that I'm here.

16:12.071 --> 16:14.539
Oh, my God, what is that?

16:15.808 --> 16:18.572
I don't want you
to take the Lord's name in vain.

16:18.644 --> 16:22.102
The f-you lady won't let me say "Oh, my God"?
Got any sugar?

16:22.181 --> 16:24.741
I will not tolerate blasphemy.

16:25.751 --> 16:28.379
And the next time,
I want you to sleep upstairs.

16:28.454 --> 16:32.254
- What if I want to take a nap?
- Upstairs. Georgia rule.

16:32.324 --> 16:34.519
God, lady, you are weird.

16:35.327 --> 16:38.558
I will wash your mouth out next time.

16:40.499 --> 16:42.865
No wonder Mom hates you.

16:46.238 --> 16:49.207
I'm glad you're here, Rachel.

16:54.213 --> 17:00.345
So, do you guys have anything better
around here than Harlan Wilson?

17:01.353 --> 17:03.583
Keep your dress on. I got you a job.

17:04.356 --> 17:06.654
- A what?
- It starts Monday.

17:06.724 --> 17:09.751
Just a brisk walk from here.
I'll wake you at seven.

17:09.828 --> 17:12.661
- I'm not working.
- One more rule.

17:12.731 --> 17:16.723
- You live here, you work.
- OK...

17:16.801 --> 17:21.829
I know that you pulled your "Georgia rule" bullshit
with my mother before she fled.

17:21.906 --> 17:25.172
But I'm not her.
And you can't tell me what to do.

17:25.243 --> 17:27.973
Rachel rule.

17:28.047 --> 17:30.345
Wash your dishes.

17:30.416 --> 17:32.611
Are you asking or telling?

17:32.684 --> 17:35.551
You finished, wash your dishes.

17:41.560 --> 17:44.757
I've never really washed a dish before.

17:50.969 --> 17:53.597
<i># Oh, I see a sunny sky</i>

17:55.441 --> 17:57.341
<i># Everytime I look into...</i>

17:57.409 --> 18:01.004
Morning. How are you?
Have you been practicing?

18:01.080 --> 18:04.311
<i># ...my friend</i>

18:04.383 --> 18:07.580
<i># Stayin' together till the end</i>

18:07.653 --> 18:11.953
<i># It's gonna be a lovely day</i>

18:12.024 --> 18:13.855
<i># It's gonna</i> be...

18:13.926 --> 18:17.157
I don't know if I can afford this one.
It's for Izzy.

18:17.229 --> 18:20.596
I'm trying to find something easier on his back.
I saw something...

18:20.666 --> 18:25.694
<i># It's gonna be a lovely day</i>

18:28.574 --> 18:29.632
Hey.

18:31.910 --> 18:34.970
- Morning.
- Morning.

18:35.047 --> 18:37.277
- Morning.
- Morning.

18:37.349 --> 18:38.816
<i># ...a lovely day</i>

18:38.884 --> 18:44.754
<i># It's gonna be a lovely day</i>

18:44.823 --> 18:47.951
Surprise.
Saddling up your truck?

18:48.026 --> 18:51.962
I had it figured
that you'd done away with Simon,

18:52.030 --> 18:55.864
buried his body and taken off for the city
with his cash and car.

18:55.934 --> 18:58.095
And leave you alive?

18:58.470 --> 19:00.938
Just how disturbed are you?

19:01.006 --> 19:03.634
I prefer "unique."

19:03.709 --> 19:06.678
- How old are you, anyway?
- Old enough.

19:07.679 --> 19:10.170
- Old enough for what?
- To disturb you.

19:11.316 --> 19:14.683
You're a dangerous girl, aren't you?

19:14.753 --> 19:17.119
It depends on what you consider dangerous.

19:17.189 --> 19:19.817
Safer to get thrown from a horse.

19:19.892 --> 19:24.955
Well, you don't have to brush or feed me
after riding me.

19:25.030 --> 19:27.021
<i>(bell chiming)</i>

19:31.303 --> 19:34.272
- I got a girl.
- <i>(dog barks)</i>

19:37.109 --> 19:39.441
Have a good day, cowboy.

19:39.511 --> 19:41.502
<i>(drums beating)</i>

19:45.184 --> 19:47.846
Fourth of July picnic this Saturday.

19:47.920 --> 19:50.320
Bring the family.

19:50.389 --> 19:54.189
- Mandy, stop us.
- Mark time. March.

19:54.259 --> 19:57.558
- Who is that?
- I don't know.

19:57.629 --> 20:00.530
Not from around here.
Move us.

20:00.599 --> 20:02.692
Forward, march.

20:02.768 --> 20:05.066
Fourth of July picnic this Saturday.

20:05.137 --> 20:08.163
Music and games.
Petting zoo for the kids.

20:08.240 --> 20:11.676
Pet a cow. Squeeze a pig.
Milk a goat.

20:11.743 --> 20:13.734
<i>(dog barks)</i>

20:16.915 --> 20:18.644
Hello?

20:18.717 --> 20:22.209
Hi. I'm here to tell you
that I won't be working here.

20:22.287 --> 20:26.485
Oh, Georgia called me about you.

20:26.558 --> 20:30.722
- Well, aren't you a pretty little thing?
- Fern. Fern.

20:31.863 --> 20:36.766
I'Iljust be a moment, dear.
If you'll stay with the phone...

20:37.469 --> 20:43.601
Very good, Violet. We don't want any accidents,
it confuses the animals. Come along.

20:43.675 --> 20:47.441
The bathroom's right in here,
you know that, Violet.

20:47.512 --> 20:48.877
<i>(man)</i> I'm all right.

20:48.947 --> 20:51.415
No lifting, Izzy.
I'm telling you, I mean it.

20:51.483 --> 20:54.577
You're not a weightlifter.
<i>(gibberish)</i>

20:54.653 --> 20:56.382
- How do you say?
- <i>(Izzy laughs)</i>

20:56.455 --> 21:00.414
Hearing the Basque language makes me feel better,
especially when I'm in pain.

21:00.492 --> 21:05.794
Hear me as your doctor. I'm telling you, no lifting.
No feedbags, no hay bales, no more cows.

21:05.864 --> 21:09.459
- I have to lift. I'm Basque.
- You're a Basque with a hernia.

21:09.534 --> 21:12.560
- No lifting, not even your own hat.
- All right...

21:12.638 --> 21:16.438
Ahem. Hi. I'm the new office girl.

21:17.509 --> 21:19.500
You're Lilly's daughter?

21:19.578 --> 21:24.948
It's a pleasure to meet you.
I am Istegui Argitalexei Sarronainda.

21:26.184 --> 21:29.119
- But you can call me Izzy.
- Mm.

21:29.187 --> 21:31.587
- Better.
- And you?

21:31.657 --> 21:34.421
- I'm Rachel. From California.
- Ah...

21:34.493 --> 21:36.620
California -
the land of fruits and nuts.

21:36.695 --> 21:38.026
<i>(chuckles)</i>

21:38.096 --> 21:41.691
- Signing out.
- I mean it. Let Harlan do your lifting.

21:43.001 --> 21:45.993
- You know Harlan?
- Yes. Hardest worker I've ever had.

21:46.071 --> 21:48.266
He lifts like a Basque.

21:48.340 --> 21:54.438
You tell Harlan that if he's up for a little danger,
then I'd really love a ride.

21:58.116 --> 21:59.777
OK.

21:59.851 --> 22:03.446
I will do that. Nice to meet you, Rachel.
Simon.

22:03.522 --> 22:05.513
- Slowly.
- Slowly, slowly...

22:09.895 --> 22:12.796
- You are the anti-Christ.
- <i>(door closes)</i>

22:12.864 --> 22:16.960
Violet Seymoure
is in the examination room for you, Doctor.

22:17.035 --> 22:19.230
- Isn't she a beauty?
- Well...

22:19.304 --> 22:21.272
- Same as Lilly.
- Sure.

22:21.340 --> 22:23.137
Yeah, mm-hmm.

22:24.876 --> 22:28.243
- He treats people?
- Unofficially.

