44:52.556 --> 44:55.616
What does this mean, Harlan?

44:55.693 --> 44:57.354
Nothing.

44:57.428 --> 45:02.832
That's what this means. June, I just wanted to
come down and be 110% honest about all of this...

45:02.900 --> 45:09.464
Just... Listen, the truth is, I took advantage of him,
OK? He had nothing to do with it.

45:09.540 --> 45:15.035
I mean, I kissed him. And he wanted to make sure
that nothing came between the two of you.

45:15.112 --> 45:18.741
And now it's over and done with,
and we're just friends.

45:18.816 --> 45:22.513
- And that's all that happened?
- Yeah, that's it.

45:27.891 --> 45:30.359
She, uh, gave me oral sex.

45:31.228 --> 45:33.219
He's lying.

45:36.100 --> 45:37.931
But we didn't kiss.

45:38.368 --> 45:40.427
June.

45:40.504 --> 45:42.165
Juniper.

45:42.239 --> 45:43.900
I mean...

45:43.974 --> 45:44.998
June bug.

45:45.075 --> 45:48.135
<i>(chiming)</i>

45:56.453 --> 46:01.015
When Dad was dying, nearly dead,
did you ever miss a meal?

46:01.091 --> 46:03.924
Eat late? Eat early?

46:03.994 --> 46:06.258
No. Same time.

46:07.297 --> 46:09.492
Alone.

46:09.566 --> 46:12.160
I could turn the radio on.

46:12.236 --> 46:13.635
<i>(# classical)</i>

46:13.704 --> 46:17.572
You're a minute late. Enjoy your meal.
I'm gonna go wait for Rachel.

46:17.975 --> 46:22.071
Life is much less of a surprise
when it's all timed down.

46:25.115 --> 46:29.609
This isn't a surprise, Mother.
This is a damn lie.

46:39.596 --> 46:41.587
<i>(# rock playing over radio)</i>

46:51.742 --> 46:53.607
Hey.

46:53.677 --> 46:55.668
Come on, we're here.

46:57.815 --> 47:03.378
So, the deal is, I can't see you,
talk to you or be anywhere near you?

47:04.855 --> 47:08.052
I wasn't exactly in the bargaining position.

47:10.327 --> 47:13.023
It's not fair.

47:14.665 --> 47:19.193
She's gonna have everyone she knows
watching me from now on.

47:21.972 --> 47:24.532
You're my only friend.

47:28.445 --> 47:30.572
OK, fine.

47:33.383 --> 47:34.350
Rachel...

47:40.157 --> 47:42.148
OK, well...

47:43.227 --> 47:44.888
...bye.

47:55.539 --> 47:57.530
Enjoy yourself?

48:02.346 --> 48:04.371
Have fun?

48:05.115 --> 48:08.312
Mom, what are you doing here?
Where's Grandma?

48:08.385 --> 48:10.683
Went to bed. I waited up for you.

48:11.488 --> 48:13.319
I have been sitting here for hours

48:13.390 --> 48:18.350
thinking how is it that I'm ever
gonna be able to forgive you?

48:18.428 --> 48:20.794
Sometimes I think the same thing
about you.

48:22.833 --> 48:29.796
And then it occurred to me a while ago
that the only weapon I have left -

48:31.108 --> 48:33.440
I've used every other -

48:37.447 --> 48:39.608
is my love for you.

48:39.683 --> 48:42.481
You could have phoned it in, Mom.

48:42.552 --> 48:46.545
- I love you.
- Did you practice that in the mirror?

48:46.623 --> 48:48.318
Wait.

48:48.392 --> 48:54.388
He thinks of you as his own daughter.
That's what I don't understand. He loves you.

48:54.464 --> 48:57.900
The question is, does he love you
how he loves me?

49:02.272 --> 49:04.433
- I want the truth.
- That's why you're here?

49:04.508 --> 49:06.533
Yeah, say it. Say it!

49:06.610 --> 49:09.773
He must have said it to you.
Why drive ten hours to hear it again?

49:09.846 --> 49:12.679
He did say it, and I believe him.

49:12.749 --> 49:16.276
I want you to say it.

49:16.353 --> 49:18.082
Rachel!

49:19.356 --> 49:25.761
I don't think you know the difference anymore,
what's right or wrong,

49:25.829 --> 49:28.525
what is a lie and what is the truth.

49:30.267 --> 49:33.259
Yeah, OK, that is my fault.

49:33.337 --> 49:37.467
I just... I didn't wanna be like my mother,

49:37.541 --> 49:39.873
with her good and bad and her rules...

49:39.943 --> 49:43.674
- Tell me what you want me to say.
- He never touched you.

49:43.747 --> 49:46.375
He never touched me.

49:46.450 --> 49:48.281
He never climbed on top of me,

49:48.352 --> 49:52.880
never put his hand on my thigh
when your head was turned at the table at dinner.

49:52.956 --> 49:56.756
He never put his mouth on my body.
Never, Mom.

49:57.794 --> 49:59.785
I said it.

50:42.339 --> 50:45.399
- I can't...
- <i>(dog barks)</i>

51:12.069 --> 51:13.229
<i>(knock on door)</i>

51:25.982 --> 51:27.973
Not right now, Grandma.

51:29.519 --> 51:31.510
I'm proud of you.

51:41.832 --> 51:45.393
Yes, such a happy morning.

51:45.469 --> 51:49.735
Yes, I have to cut your nails. Yes, I do.

51:49.806 --> 51:53.139
They're getting a little long.
<i>(coos)</i>

51:57.647 --> 51:59.080
<i>(door closes)</i>

52:14.598 --> 52:16.964
When did it start?

52:17.033 --> 52:19.934
- When I was 12.
- When did it stop?

52:22.772 --> 52:25.832
When a friend of mine
threatened to kill him.

52:25.909 --> 52:28.343
That's when I was 14.

52:28.411 --> 52:33.940
He bought me the Mustang on the condition
that I start again, so I crashed it.

52:34.017 --> 52:36.781
Rachel? Ha-

52:38.722 --> 52:41.589
Ham and cheese. One's for Simon.

52:41.658 --> 52:43.649
Here you go.

52:45.629 --> 52:47.620
Yeah, have a nice day.

52:55.172 --> 53:00.132
If you're not in for breakfast in 15 minutes,
you'll have to wait for lunch.

53:03.713 --> 53:05.704
<i>(chirping)</i>

53:18.762 --> 53:20.855
Let's go, kids. It's open.

53:22.399 --> 53:24.526
Go like this. Ready? Hold my hand.

53:24.601 --> 53:29.163
You go like this. A circle.
You can use other colors.

53:29.239 --> 53:31.673
- Good. That's pretty.
- Thanks so much, Rachel.

53:31.741 --> 53:36.940
- Oh, you're welcome.
- We will not bite Mommy's ear again, will we? No.

53:37.013 --> 53:39.777
- Bye. Thanks.
- Bye. Good to see you.

53:40.650 --> 53:44.746
- Thanks, Mr. Wells. I'm sure we'll see you again.
- Thank you, Doc.

53:44.821 --> 53:46.618
Hello.

53:46.690 --> 53:48.920
That is $25, sir.

53:48.992 --> 53:51.984
No. Doc usually just sends me a bill
now and then.

53:52.062 --> 53:56.260
Unless you've made prior arrangements,
then it's $25, today.

53:56.900 --> 54:01.064
- Where's Fern?
- She's on vacation. I'm not really sure.

54:01.137 --> 54:02.798
Cash or check?

54:02.872 --> 54:08.071
- This is not the way we usually do it around here.
- Well, I'm new.

54:08.144 --> 54:10.339
It shows.

54:10.413 --> 54:13.780
I've written "paid in full" on your receipt.

54:13.850 --> 54:19.880
I'll let you take these as a reminder.
They're copies of your previous unpaid bills.

54:19.956 --> 54:22.447
- When's Fern coming back?
- No idea.

54:22.525 --> 54:25.858
- I'll send you a weekly reminder until they're paid.
- Thank you.

54:25.929 --> 54:28.659
- Welcome.
- I'm not happy, Andy.

54:28.732 --> 54:30.723
Have a good day.

54:31.701 --> 54:38.072
Amazing. I haven't got a nickel out of him
in four years, and you get $25 in two minutes.

54:38.141 --> 54:39.631
I'm good at getting.

54:40.243 --> 54:42.575
- I'll be right with you, Mr. Lynwood.
- <i>(squawks)</i>

54:42.646 --> 54:44.773
<i>(# guitar)</i>

54:48.418 --> 54:51.285
How long have you been doing that for?

54:52.255 --> 54:54.280
Since college.

54:54.357 --> 54:56.985
It relaxes me. I just play for myself.

54:58.061 --> 55:01.861
- Have you dated since your wife passed away?
- Hasn't entered my mind.

55:01.931 --> 55:03.990
<i>(plucks strings)</i>

55:04.067 --> 55:07.525
- You know, I used to date your mother.
- I know.

55:09.172 --> 55:12.005
In fact, I was crazy about her.

55:12.776 --> 55:15.677
Why didn't you marry her,
save us all the trouble?

55:15.745 --> 55:19.977
Things don't always work out
the way you think they should.

55:20.050 --> 55:22.314
But you know about that.

55:22.385 --> 55:26.617
Wait. That's weird.
So you could have been my dad.

55:26.690 --> 55:28.885
Your dad had a car. I had a cow.

55:28.958 --> 55:32.416
Huh. It's always about a car.
Pizza's ready.

55:34.164 --> 55:36.155
<i>(phone ringing)</i>

55:40.870 --> 55:44.431
At least talk to him long enough
to tell him you're not talking to him.

55:44.507 --> 55:46.372
Just pick up and hang up.

55:46.443 --> 55:49.810
Pick up and hang up,
pick up and hang up and so on.

55:49.879 --> 55:53.212
Do you have anything this size

55:53.283 --> 55:55.683
that's serrated, hmm?

55:55.752 --> 55:58.880
He's got thick skin.

55:58.955 --> 56:00.217
<i>(scoffs)</i> Hmm?

56:05.028 --> 56:07.496
You know what's hysterical about all this?

56:08.431 --> 56:10.763
I signed a prenuptial.

56:10.834 --> 56:13.428
I'm going to end up back here

56:13.503 --> 56:19.203
with nothing and no one,
living in a place I am not welcome.

56:19.275 --> 56:22.073
Who says you're not welcome?

56:22.879 --> 56:24.608
Your face.

56:27.050 --> 56:30.417
At least he'll be in prison.

56:30.487 --> 56:33.320
Arnold is one of the best
criminal defense lawyers

56:33.390 --> 56:35.881
in California, Mother.

56:35.959 --> 56:42.364
He's not gonna end up anywhere but free,
happy, laughing and playing golf.

56:45.435 --> 56:47.426
Go with this one.

56:55.044 --> 56:57.535
So, did you know my real dad?

56:59.716 --> 57:03.345
He was exactly what you wouldn't want
a daughter to marry.

57:03.420 --> 57:07.789
Lilly was angry with everybody, even me,
when she left with him.

57:07.857 --> 57:11.725
- How could you even stand her?
- She reminds me of you.

57:11.795 --> 57:13.786
I know.

57:14.264 --> 57:16.425
There.

57:18.201 --> 57:21.432
- Do you wanna hear something weird?
- Probably not.

57:22.639 --> 57:25.699
When Arnold held me, I hated the sex.

57:27.143 --> 57:31.546
But then, sometimes before,
when he just held me,

57:33.516 --> 57:36.246
I felt loved.

57:36.319 --> 57:39.254
And I... I mean, how can that be true?

57:40.690 --> 57:45.024
Maybe the holding part was love, Rachel.
I'm not sure.

57:46.963 --> 57:49.193
But I know everything else was a lie.

57:54.604 --> 57:57.835
I'm gonna show you the top to this stupid thing
so we can finish it.

57:57.907 --> 57:58.999
- I won't look.
- Here.

57:59.075 --> 58:00.804
I'm not looking.

58:00.877 --> 58:04.643
How can you do a puzzle,
if you don't know what it looks like?

58:04.714 --> 58:10.414
It's like telling you how your life will end.
It makes everything in between killing time.

58:10.487 --> 58:13.513
- Go home.
- I don't wanna go home.

58:13.590 --> 58:16.388
You can't stay here. Good night.

58:25.001 --> 58:28.095
<i>(clock chiming)</i>

58:34.344 --> 58:36.335
Time for bed.

58:39.582 --> 58:41.573
<i>(dog barking)</i>

58:42.619 --> 58:44.610
<i>(footsteps, running)</i>

59:02.539 --> 59:06.134
I found these in the closet.

59:07.110 --> 59:10.568
- I thought they'd be safer there.
- <i>(giggles)</i>

59:10.647 --> 59:17.644
Most people dig out presents they don't like
when the person that gave them comes to visit.

59:18.721 --> 59:21.417
I don't keep flowers in the house.

59:22.292 --> 59:25.728
It's two past ten, Mother. Go to bed.

59:32.135 --> 59:33.397
<i>(gasps)</i>

59:35.104 --> 59:36.765
Oh, come on.

59:38.041 --> 59:41.772
There was a time you'd have dragged me
by hair for drinking.

59:41.844 --> 59:45.473
I'm too old. So's your hair.

59:45.548 --> 59:48.517
<i>(snickers)</i> That's good.

59:48.585 --> 59:50.576
<i>(water running)</i>

59:53.156 --> 59:55.488
These go here.

59:55.558 --> 59:56.957
Here. There.

01:00:04.500 --> 01:00:05.558
<i>(Lilly)</i> Oh.

01:00:06.936 --> 01:00:07.664
<i>(Lilly)</i> Whoo.

01:00:08.972 --> 01:00:12.237
- Whoo- ooh-ooh.
- Come here. Let me take you to bed.

01:00:12.308 --> 01:00:17.007
You don't get second chances.
Don't try and save me. I'm not savable.

01:00:17.080 --> 01:00:19.674
Everybody's savable. That's the rule.

01:00:19.749 --> 01:00:25.619
Screw your rules. I begged you, "Please, Mommy"
for help at Daddy's funeral.

01:00:25.688 --> 01:00:30.990
And that's when I needed saving, Mother,
but, no, you wouldn't give me a cent.

01:00:31.060 --> 01:00:35.622
- You were drinking.
- I was alone with a four year old. I was scared.

01:00:35.698 --> 01:00:39.156
Arnold saved us. Arnold saved me.

01:00:39.235 --> 01:00:41.863
I wanted you to stay.

01:00:41.938 --> 01:00:44.805
I wanted you to die.

01:00:52.115 --> 01:00:54.447
Not really.

01:00:54.517 --> 01:00:56.178
Just a little.

01:00:57.286 --> 01:00:59.686
Why do you need to hurt her?

01:01:01.224 --> 01:01:03.590
Because you slept with my husband.

01:01:10.867 --> 01:01:13.358
- Rachel... Aah!
- <i>(glass shatters)</i>

01:01:13.436 --> 01:01:15.631
Mom?

01:01:15.705 --> 01:01:18.037
Grandma. I need help.

01:01:18.107 --> 01:01:19.972
- I'll handle it.
- I didn't touch her.

01:01:20.043 --> 01:01:22.341
- Don't touch me.
- Go to your room.

01:01:22.412 --> 01:01:27.782
- Why did you let her start again?
- I can handle it. Leave me with her. Go.

01:01:30.853 --> 01:01:32.844
Let me look.

01:01:35.425 --> 01:01:38.724
- Careful of the glass. Can you get up?
- Mm-hmm.

01:01:38.795 --> 01:01:42.060
- I am getting up. Where we going?
- I'm gonna put you in bed...

01:01:42.131 --> 01:01:44.599
and I'm gonna give you an aspirin.

01:01:44.667 --> 01:01:48.262
I'm good. I'm gonna make this. OK.

01:01:48.337 --> 01:01:51.738
I'm gonna...
I'm good...

01:01:51.808 --> 01:01:55.039
- Whoa, I'm gonna throw up.
- Not on the rug.

01:01:55.111 --> 01:01:58.979
Let me help. I've done this before.
Come on, Mom.

01:02:01.350 --> 01:02:05.286
This is good. This is good.
<i>(giggles)</i>

01:02:05.354 --> 01:02:09.791
Lilly, can you make it upstairs
without throwing up, please?

01:02:09.859 --> 01:02:11.850
<i>(# harmonica)</i>

01:02:21.437 --> 01:02:23.428
I am fishing.

01:02:23.506 --> 01:02:26.566
It's just me and my dog.

01:02:27.543 --> 01:02:31.479
And Rachel's not here,
and I'm not happy about it.

01:02:33.816 --> 01:02:36.011
The doctor won't hurt you. It's OK.

01:02:46.229 --> 01:02:49.255
I don't know, Melody.
He seems like a pretty calm pig.

01:02:49.332 --> 01:02:55.100
Yeah, right now, but then, suddenly, he gets
alljumpy, starts running around and squealing,

01:02:55.171 --> 01:02:57.662
and he disrupts the other pigs.

01:02:57.740 --> 01:03:00.334
- You think it's stress?
- Pig stress?

01:03:12.855 --> 01:03:14.846
Slut.

01:03:15.525 --> 01:03:17.356
Slut!

01:03:37.380 --> 01:03:40.577
I gotta get to work.
I got that lasso in for you.

01:03:41.684 --> 01:03:46.678
- He doesn't think I'm pretty. He doesn't like me.
- No, he likes Trouble, on the bench over there.

01:03:49.292 --> 01:03:51.283
<i>(water runs)</i>

01:04:00.570 --> 01:04:02.299
Where's Rachel?

01:04:02.371 --> 01:04:04.362
- At Simon's.
- Goody.

01:04:04.440 --> 01:04:07.807
I told her to go there till you're better.
Where you going?

01:04:07.877 --> 01:04:12.143
- I'm going for a drive.
- You're not dressed for a drive.

01:04:12.215 --> 01:04:14.683
I'm thirsty, OK? I'm dying of thirst.

01:04:14.750 --> 01:04:19.881
I'm waking up, I can't stand the feeling.
I'm gonna go buy booze, busybody.

01:04:20.456 --> 01:04:24.688
- It wasn't a question.
- No more drinking in the house. Georgia rule.

01:04:24.760 --> 01:04:29.220
Mother, let me go.
I don't care about your rules. Fuck off.

01:04:30.499 --> 01:04:32.592
Get off me. Get off me!

01:04:36.138 --> 01:04:39.369
All right, all right.

01:04:42.345 --> 01:04:46.645
I called Arnold last night,
and I asked him for a divorce.

01:04:48.217 --> 01:04:50.208
OK, Mother?

01:04:52.788 --> 01:04:54.551
You lost your...

01:04:57.193 --> 01:04:59.184
My mind?

01:05:00.496 --> 01:05:02.293
I'll get the booze.

01:05:02.365 --> 01:05:04.356
Go inside.

01:05:10.806 --> 01:05:12.797
Thank you.

01:05:18.447 --> 01:05:20.642
Have a nice party, Georgia.

01:05:31.594 --> 01:05:33.425
"A in Science" for $2,000, please...

01:05:33.496 --> 01:05:39.867
- Thanks for letting me stay over tonight.
- Well, Georgia thought it might be a good idea.

01:05:40.636 --> 01:05:42.501
What's an Allosaurus?

01:05:42.571 --> 01:05:46.302
- I think it's a good idea.
- "Heraldic Beasts", $400, please.

01:05:46.375 --> 01:05:49.242
I found some perfume under the sink.

01:05:50.313 --> 01:05:52.611
I didn't think you'd mind it.

01:05:53.582 --> 01:05:58.076
- I forgot I still had that.
- It's next to your stash of toilet paper.

01:05:58.154 --> 01:06:01.646
- Every time you change a roll, you see it.
- What's the Loch Ness Monster?

01:06:01.724 --> 01:06:05.387
- No. Doug?
- What's an elephant?

01:06:05.461 --> 01:06:08.897
- Do you ever smell it?
- No, I try not to.

01:06:08.965 --> 01:06:11.866
Do you think she'd want you to?

01:06:11.934 --> 01:06:13.925
- Erika?
- Who is Ginsberg?

01:06:14.003 --> 01:06:15.766
"Poets" for $1200, please.

01:06:15.838 --> 01:06:21.299
Poem containing the line "Perched upon
a bust of Pallas just above my chamber door."

01:06:21.377 --> 01:06:23.607
- What is "The Raven?"
- Right.

01:06:23.679 --> 01:06:27.206
- "Poets," $1600, please.
- Can I ask you a favor?

01:06:27.283 --> 01:06:29.342
During the commercial.

01:06:30.920 --> 01:06:32.911
Can I hold on to you?

01:06:33.889 --> 01:06:37.017
- Hold on to me?
- Just lean against you.

01:06:39.128 --> 01:06:42.655
I just like to feel somebody next to me.

01:06:42.732 --> 01:06:46.498
- "Beasts" for $1200.
- This animal is on the Lopez family coat of arms,

01:06:46.569 --> 01:06:50.767
probably because the name Lopez
comes from the Latin for it.

01:06:50.840 --> 01:06:53.570
- What is a wolf?
- Kathleen. Yes.

01:06:53.642 --> 01:06:55.837
Can I ask you another favor?

01:06:56.746 --> 01:06:58.304
What?

01:06:58.381 --> 01:07:00.372
Relax.

01:07:04.987 --> 01:07:09.481
I'm gonna go to bed.
There are blankets and pillows in the closet.

01:07:11.827 --> 01:07:13.761
<i>(knock on door)</i>

01:07:13.829 --> 01:07:16.354
You're gonna have to eat something sometime.

01:07:19.035 --> 01:07:21.196
I'm gonna open the door.

01:07:29.512 --> 01:07:34.108
- Oh, you cut your hair.
- It was getting in the way of my drinking.

01:07:37.219 --> 01:07:41.622
All I remember are Dad's hugs,

01:07:41.690 --> 01:07:43.419
his laugh.

01:07:43.492 --> 01:07:47.121
After all of it, just good things.

01:07:47.196 --> 01:07:49.187
Well, good.

01:07:49.265 --> 01:07:53.463
Why did you try so hard
to take that away from me?

01:07:53.536 --> 01:07:56.096
- Did I?
- Little things.

01:07:56.172 --> 01:07:59.539
We loved to watch TV together,
so you took it away.

01:07:59.608 --> 01:08:03.442
Television was a distraction.
Your grades were slipping.

01:08:03.512 --> 01:08:07.039
Were you afraid how much
Daddy and I were alike?

01:08:07.116 --> 01:08:11.450
How much he relied on me?
How little he wanted from you?

01:08:12.388 --> 01:08:17.381
You know, mostly... I was afraid
you'd run off and marry an idiot,

01:08:17.460 --> 01:08:21.692
lose everything you had a chance at,
just like me.

01:08:23.365 --> 01:08:25.629
I blamed you for his drinking.

01:08:26.769 --> 01:08:28.828
Oh. For yours, too?

01:08:30.439 --> 01:08:31.337
Yeah.

01:08:34.777 --> 01:08:38.679
You know what I don't understand,
along with all the rest of it?

01:08:38.747 --> 01:08:40.738
I haven't got a clue.

01:08:41.850 --> 01:08:45.343
- If you ever really loved me.
- <i>(scoffs)</i>

01:08:45.421 --> 01:08:46.911
Don't be ridiculous.

01:08:46.988 --> 01:08:51.551
No, I mean, just ever.
It wouldn't have to include right now.

01:08:51.627 --> 01:08:53.685
What do you think the rules were?

01:08:53.761 --> 01:08:59.131
Why would I waste my time
on somebody that I didn't care about?

01:09:00.336 --> 01:09:07.071
Yeah. I can't ever remember
you saying it.

01:09:07.643 --> 01:09:09.634
Well, my parents never said it.

01:09:09.712 --> 01:09:12.475
So how do you know if they did?

01:09:13.782 --> 01:09:15.773
I don't.

01:09:25.928 --> 01:09:30.991
I hate that you bought me so many.

01:09:32.734 --> 01:09:35.328
You gonna drink the rest of them?

01:09:36.505 --> 01:09:37.163
No.

01:10:05.067 --> 01:10:07.228
How could I not love you?

01:10:28.023 --> 01:10:28.887
Rachel?

01:10:29.358 --> 01:10:31.417
It's just Dr. Ward today.

01:10:32.928 --> 01:10:38.764
- She just needs a little more exercise, more walks.
- You hear that, Bertha?

01:10:38.834 --> 01:10:42.270
Come on. Hey.
Just have to cut out on the snacking.

01:10:44.306 --> 01:10:46.433
Tell her she's fat.

01:10:46.508 --> 01:10:48.373
You are fat.

01:10:48.444 --> 01:10:53.040
See what I told you?
He's a doctor. It's not just me saying it.

01:10:53.115 --> 01:10:55.106
- Thanks, Dr. Ward.
- Sure.

01:10:58.621 --> 01:11:01.112
You look great with short hair.

01:11:06.595 --> 01:11:09.530
- Where's Rachel?
- It's Saturday. I gave her the day off.

01:11:09.598 --> 01:11:11.998
She went fishing with Harlan.

01:11:15.337 --> 01:11:18.170
I need to stop drinking.

01:11:19.275 --> 01:11:21.266
I'm in no hurry.

01:11:22.244 --> 01:11:26.044
- How can I help?
- She's pregnant, is all.

01:11:28.484 --> 01:11:32.113
Why don't you wait in the office?
This'll take a second.

01:11:32.187 --> 01:11:34.178
<i>(radio playing)</i>

01:11:37.326 --> 01:11:40.295
She's got that California tan.

01:11:40.362 --> 01:11:44.731
- You think it's real or a spray-on?
- I don't know.

01:11:45.200 --> 01:11:50.934
- It's risky being my friend.
- Well, that's what I was coming around to is...

01:11:51.006 --> 01:11:54.271
maybe we could be more than friends, you know,

01:11:54.343 --> 01:11:57.244
if you thought you could ever sort of -

01:11:58.247 --> 01:11:59.976
I don't know -

01:12:00.049 --> 01:12:01.914
love me?

01:12:06.789 --> 01:12:08.950
I'm kicking men, Harlan.

01:12:10.526 --> 01:12:15.122
No, really. So I guess that's what
I was trying to say - kicking men.

01:12:15.197 --> 01:12:19.531
Yeah, well, I'll be gone for two years
on this mission.

01:12:20.869 --> 01:12:23.463
You can't kick forever, can you?

01:12:25.507 --> 01:12:27.168
I promise I'll write.

01:12:27.876 --> 01:12:32.438
I think they're going. Get on the cellphone.
Call the girls. Let's follow her.

01:12:35.551 --> 01:12:39.851
More kittens.
As if this town needs more cats.

01:12:39.922 --> 01:12:41.913
And that was my last patient.

01:12:45.194 --> 01:12:47.685
- <i>(clock chiming)</i>
- Remember the clock tower?

01:12:47.763 --> 01:12:50.994
- I do. Do you?
- Like it was yesterday.

01:12:51.066 --> 01:12:53.159
We changed the clock back.

01:12:53.836 --> 01:12:56.168
Yeah, yeah.

01:12:56.238 --> 01:13:01.039
And the whole day,
the whole town was just a mess.

01:13:02.010 --> 01:13:04.410
Except you. You weren't a mess.

01:13:04.480 --> 01:13:07.040
Anyway, um...

01:13:07.116 --> 01:13:09.448
I need Antabuse.

01:13:10.819 --> 01:13:13.447
That makes you violently ill if you drink.

01:13:13.522 --> 01:13:15.717
I already am violently ill.

01:13:18.160 --> 01:13:21.857
I'm going to Rexburg later.
I'll pick some up.

01:13:21.930 --> 01:13:23.921
Thanks.

01:13:25.634 --> 01:13:27.625
Is that all you need?

01:13:29.838 --> 01:13:32.500
How did I miss what I missed?

01:13:34.877 --> 01:13:36.970
People get busy.

01:13:37.045 --> 01:13:42.449
Too busy to notice
what your husband is doing to your daughter?

01:13:42.518 --> 01:13:44.509
I don't know how you missed that.

01:13:46.488 --> 01:13:48.683
You always tell me the truth.

01:13:49.825 --> 01:13:51.816
Thank you.

01:14:24.693 --> 01:14:27.025
- What was that?
- I'm sorry.

01:14:28.430 --> 01:14:29.522
No...

01:14:31.467 --> 01:14:33.332
Thank you. Thank you.

01:14:34.036 --> 01:14:36.027
I gotta go.

01:15:01.463 --> 01:15:04.159
How long do we have to sit here for?

01:15:05.267 --> 01:15:07.258
Smells like rain.

01:15:08.937 --> 01:15:11.667
OK. Let's do it. Mandy, get ready.

01:15:15.777 --> 01:15:18.075
Give us a break, Grace.

01:15:18.146 --> 01:15:20.137
Let's go.

01:15:22.351 --> 01:15:23.750
Car won't start.

01:15:27.122 --> 01:15:28.316
Whoa. Oh.

01:15:30.959 --> 01:15:34.520
- She's gonna ram us.
- Oh, my God. Get out. Go.

01:15:35.397 --> 01:15:37.763
<i>(truck radio blasting)</i>

01:15:56.818 --> 01:16:00.379
Hi. Want to introduce myself.
Rachel Wilcox. Nice to meet you.

01:16:00.455 --> 01:16:03.151
- Grace Cunningham.
- Howdy, girls. How you doing?

01:16:03.225 --> 01:16:08.663
Look, I just drove over to tell you
that Harlan and I, we're just friends now.

01:16:08.730 --> 01:16:12.063
Nothing's gonna happen again.
I promise. Scout's honor.

01:16:12.134 --> 01:16:16.537
So you guys can go and do whatever it is you do,
have your summer fun.

01:16:16.605 --> 01:16:20.041
And tell June that we're apart,
even if we're not,

01:16:20.108 --> 01:16:22.702
'cause nothing's gonna happen,
and whatever's happened has happened already,

01:16:22.778 --> 01:16:25.269
so that's the end of it.

01:16:25.347 --> 01:16:29.306
Fine. Then why don't you just go home
and leave us all alone?

01:16:29.885 --> 01:16:34.413
OK, I tried to be nice. Let me put this a different way,
'cause you're not getting it.

01:16:34.489 --> 01:16:38.255
If you call me a name,
if you throw something at me ever again,

01:16:38.327 --> 01:16:43.162
if I see you talking to Harlan, yelling at Harlan,
having anything at all to do with Harlan,

01:16:43.231 --> 01:16:47.634
I will find all of your boyfriends,
and I will fuck them stupid.

01:16:49.871 --> 01:16:52.601
OK? Get it?

01:16:53.141 --> 01:16:55.609
Thanks for your time.
Have a good summer.

01:16:56.878 --> 01:17:00.871
- I am gonna pray for her.
- <i>(thunder crashes)</i>

01:17:02.117 --> 01:17:03.141
Harlan.

